857
00:50:45.684 --> 00:50:48.464
Third, a closed system that enables,

858
00:50:50.064 --> 00:50:53.564
essentially, that resistance to develop without additional

859
00:50:53.664 --> 00:50:56.104
unnecessary perturbations to the system,

860
00:50:57.124 --> 00:51:01.114
and that introduce artificial or artifacts in terms

861
00:51:01.184 --> 00:51:05.004
of evolutionary bottlenecks. And finally, we need the resolution to

862
00:51:05.044 --> 00:51:08.704
resolve clonal selection over time at the single-cell level,

863
00:51:09.024 --> 00:51:13.004
so we can recapitulate minimal residual disease dynamics in

864
00:51:13.063 --> 00:51:13.604
the clinic,

865
00:51:14.424 --> 00:51:17.824
where relapse often starts, as you've heard from Dr.

866
00:51:18.104 --> 00:51:21.824
Galsky and Dr. Abash, from just a few cancer cells that is

867
00:51:21.984 --> 00:51:24.794
what's underlying this ctDNA or cfDNA.

868
00:51:26.044 --> 00:51:29.844
So to capture these elements, we developed a system that we call

869
00:51:29.884 --> 00:51:33.724
Evolutionary Single-Cell Genomics RNA and Lineage Tracking

