893
00:52:54.984 --> 00:52:58.604
Cornell. And you can see on the right that this was also

894
00:52:58.664 --> 00:53:02.524
quantified across all patients in the cohort and confirms

895
00:53:02.564 --> 00:53:05.184
that APOBEC activity is early and clonal.

896
00:53:05.404 --> 00:53:09.224
So again, before the patient sees any treatment, there's a lot of APOBEC

897
00:53:09.284 --> 00:53:09.804
activity.

898
00:53:10.764 --> 00:53:14.724
So we hypothesized that this early APOBEC-3A, or A3A for

899
00:53:14.784 --> 00:53:18.264
short, which I'll refer to by A3 in the rest of the talk,

900
00:53:19.304 --> 00:53:23.064
this induced heterogeneity by A3A drives therapy resistance.

901
00:53:24.164 --> 00:53:25.644
So to model this, we

902
00:53:27.024 --> 00:53:30.984
used a cell line called a 5637 bladder cancer cell line with

903
00:53:31.024 --> 00:53:34.964
a doxycycline-inducible A3A expression vector, and

904
00:53:35.004 --> 00:53:38.504
we established isogenic clones exposed to six cycles of

905
00:53:38.524 --> 00:53:42.444
doxycycline to induce A3A or DMSO controls,

906
00:53:42.484 --> 00:53:44.964
which were then labeled with the cell tag barcodes.

907
00:53:45.424 --> 00:53:48.564
And the 5637 line harbors an ERBB2

908
00:53:48.704 --> 00:53:52.404
S310F activating mutation, so it shows initial

909
00:53:52.484 --> 00:53:56.024
sensitivity to the tyrosine kinase inhibitor neratinib.

910
00:53:56.584 --> 00:54:00.344
So we used continuous neratinib treatment on these

911
00:54:00.384 --> 00:54:03.754
cells for 35 days. Again, there's no trypsinization or any other

912
00:54:03.784 --> 00:54:07.704
perturbation as a selective pressure that is applied to one

913
00:54:07.824 --> 00:54:11.744
billion A3A-exposed and isogenic control cells in our Evo

